Built by German company TAKRA in 1995, Bagger 293 is one of the biggest terrestrial vehicles on earth. After being acquired by its current owner RWE Power AG, the second-largest energy producer in Germany, the excavator was renamed from MAN TAKRAF RB293 to Bagger 293.⁣
